Burgeoning bureaucracy and chronic underfunding take resources from classrooms and lead to the death spiral of school closure and privatization. Currently, we have some communities that can guarantee that every school will provide every student an excellent education. But many Alameda County kids are left out. They live in communities where schools have been hollowed out by chronic underinvestment, and families are left to navigate the bewildering panoply of bussing, lotteries, charter schools that open and close â€” all dressed up as choices. Kids deserve guarantees, not choices.
